<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The prevalence of
chronic heart failure averages 0.8% among the 50-59 age group and increases in
the 80-89 age group to 6.6 and 7.9% for men and women, respectively.&nbsp;The
most common cause of CHF - arterial hypertension - accounts for 95% of cases,
in second place is coronary heart disease and myocardial infarction - in third.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
